From: Artemii Karasev <karasev@ispras.ru>
Date: Thu, 19 Jan 2023 00:22:59 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] ALSA: hda/via: Avoid potential array out-of-bound in
 add_secret_dac_path()
Git-commit: b9cee506da2b7920b5ea02ccd8e78a907d0ee7aa
Patch-mainline: v6.2-rc7
References: CVE-2023-52988 bsc#1240293

snd_hda_get_connections() can return a negative error code.
It may lead to accessing 'conn' array at a negative index.

Found by Linux Verification Center (linuxtesting.org) with SVACE.

Signed-off-by: Artemii Karasev <karasev@ispras.ru>
Fixes: 30b4503378c9 ("ALSA: hda - Expose secret DAC-AA connection of some VIA codecs")
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20230119082259.3634-1-karasev@ispras.ru
Signed-off-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
---
 sound/pci/hda/patch_via.c |    3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

--- a/sound/pci/hda/patch_via.c
+++ b/sound/pci/hda/patch_via.c
@@ -834,6 +834,9 @@ static int add_secret_dac_path(struct hd
 		return 0;
 	nums = snd_hda_get_connections(codec, spec->gen.mixer_nid, conn,
 				       ARRAY_SIZE(conn) - 1);
+	if (nums < 0)
+		return nums;
+
 	for (i = 0; i < nums; i++) {
 		if (get_wcaps_type(get_wcaps(codec, conn[i])) == AC_WID_AUD_OUT)
 			return 0;
